<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Blemish1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Blemish,</orth> subst., anything that disfigures, spot, stain: <cit><quote>on their garments not a b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 218</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>speaking thick, which nature made his b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 24</bibl></cit>. Mostly in a moral sense: <cit><quote>the b. that will never be forgot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 536" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 536</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he spied in her some b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 536" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 536</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.401" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 401</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.341" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 341</bibl>. Plural: <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 3, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.59" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 13, 59</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>